    <fr:title text="Writing a vector as a linear combination of an orthonormal basis">Writing a vector as a linear combination of an orthonormal basis</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>theorem</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Theorem 6.30</fr:meta>
    <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Theorem 9.4.6</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be a finite-dimensional <fr:link href="/vectsp-0020/" title="Inner product space" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-0020/" display-uri="vectsp-0020" type="local">Inner product space</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(e_{1},…,e_{n})]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/vectsp-002D/" title="Orthonormal Basis" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-002D/" display-uri="vectsp-002D" type="local">Orthonormal Basis</fr:link> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. Then for any vector <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v\in  V]]></fr:tex>, we have
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[v = \langle  v,e_{1}\rangle  e_{1} + … + \langle  v,e_{n}\rangle  e_{n}.]]></fr:tex></html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
