            <fr:title text="Orthonormal Basis">Orthonormal Basis</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/axler-1996-linear/" title="Linear Algebra Done Right" uri="http://localhost:8000/axler-1996-linear/" display-uri="axler-1996-linear" type="local">Linear Algebra Done Right</fr:link> Definition 6.22</fr:meta>
            <fr:meta name="source"><fr:link href="/lankham-2016-linear/" title="Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics" uri="http://localhost:8000/lankham-2016-linear/" display-uri="lankham-2016-linear" type="local">Linear algebra as an introduction to abstract mathematics</fr:link> Definition 9.4.1 and 9.4.3</fr:meta>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/vectsp-0020/" title="Inner product space" uri="http://localhost:8000/vectsp-0020/" display-uri="vectsp-0020" type="local">Inner product space</fr:link> over <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be a basis of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex>. We say the basis <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is <html:dfn>Orthonormal</html:dfn> if for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[e_{i},e_{j}\in  B]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\langle  e_{i},e_{j}\rangle =\delta _{i,j}]]></fr:tex> is the Kronecker delta <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _{i,j}=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\neq  j]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\delta _{i,i}=1]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
